1
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:42,200
<i>Techut rushed setting up the department</i>
<i>and took control of everything.</i>

2
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:45,800
<i>Find the hard drive.</i>
<i>If anyone gets in the way,</i>

3
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:47,600
just kill them all.

4
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:56,680
- <i>Thank you.</i>
- <i>I only helped you</i>

5
00:02:56,760 --> 00:02:58,600
<i>because you're still useful to me.</i>

6
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:21,320
You sure are nosy.

7
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:25,200
What do you do for a living?

8
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:28,120
- I'm a hacker.
- Huh?

9
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:30,880
- Really?
- What?

10
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:32,000
Don't believe me?

11
00:03:33,520 --> 00:03:34,400
Or is it because

12
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:36,640
I'm too handsome?

13
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:42,160
Ugh! Now I'm sleepy.
Now I wanna go to bed.

14
00:03:45,760 --> 00:03:49,000
Wanna sleep on my chest? It's warm.

15
00:03:49,760 --> 00:03:50,800
Wanna try?

16
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:53,680
Aw, you're such a flirt.

17
00:03:55,040 --> 00:03:56,200
No, thanks!

18
00:07:09,960 --> 00:07:11,120
I'm sorry.

19
00:07:12,280 --> 00:07:13,640
I didn't sleep well last night.

20
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:22,320
Do you have nightmares often?

21
00:07:23,080 --> 00:07:24,280
Yeah.

22
00:07:25,560 --> 00:07:27,880
Come sit here. The sky
looks pretty from this angle.

23
00:07:32,080 --> 00:07:33,280
It looks pretty here too.

24
00:07:35,880 --> 00:07:37,520
- Come here!
- Don't! Hey!

25
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:48,360
Whenever my dad taught me how to draw,

26
00:07:49,080 --> 00:07:52,560
we'd usually go out of town
and just lie there watching the sky.

27
00:07:55,280 --> 00:07:57,960
My dad told me that
in our lives, there are mountains

28
00:07:58,480 --> 00:08:00,680
and valleys in a vast universe,

29
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:02,360
and there's a hidden power.

30
00:08:06,280 --> 00:08:08,240
That's why some people are inseparable.

31
00:08:09,320 --> 00:08:13,320
They're pulled together
by an enormous force. Do you believe that?

32
00:08:23,840 --> 00:08:24,880
No way.

33
00:08:25,840 --> 00:08:27,000
I'm not an artist.

34
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:32,720
You have a degree in financial economics?

35
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:35,800
Yes, I can also code.

36
00:09:35,880 --> 00:09:37,920
We'll test your technical skills too.

37
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:39,440
Sure.

38
00:09:55,480 --> 00:09:56,480
‪Looks good.

39
00:10:08,280 --> 00:10:11,880
The person who hurt you
can go in and out of 3C.

40
00:10:13,080 --> 00:10:14,280
Who do you suspect?

41
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:18,640
I don't know.

42
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:24,560
Is there anything you want to tell me?

43
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:52,800
Someone I know,
Naruban's bodyguard, went missing.

44
00:10:53,960 --> 00:10:56,160
- Rin?
- She ran off with your designer.

45
00:10:57,040 --> 00:11:01,680
Mr. Taiga called his staff, saying
he's going away to find inspiration.

46
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:04,760
But I didn't know
he went with someone you know.

47
00:11:04,840 --> 00:11:08,200
Normally, Rin always
stays close to Mr. Naruban.

48
00:11:08,280 --> 00:11:12,560
I bet it's something really urgent.
Otherwise, she wouldn't just disappear.

49
00:11:12,640 --> 00:11:14,640
Your employee took the girl I know.

50
00:11:16,120 --> 00:11:19,480
Can you tell Taiga to stop?
Make him stay away from Rin.

51
00:11:22,160 --> 00:11:25,480
What if those two want to be together?

52
00:11:27,560 --> 00:11:28,880
That can't happen!

53
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:33,080
No one can stop

54
00:11:33,760 --> 00:11:34,880
someone else's heart,

55
00:11:35,560 --> 00:11:36,920
and no one can stop love.

56
00:11:39,920 --> 00:11:42,800
I can't guarantee that I can help you

57
00:11:42,880 --> 00:11:47,360
because Rin seems to be hiding
her closeness to Taiga from everyone.

58
00:11:49,720 --> 00:11:53,320
But I'll try to do my best,
like you asked me to.

59
00:12:07,480 --> 00:12:08,880
<i>Rin called to ask for some days off.</i>

60
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:10,960
She needs to visit a sick relative.

61
00:12:11,040 --> 00:12:12,320
Where?

62
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:15,240
In another province.

63
00:12:16,640 --> 00:12:19,080
I told her to stay
until her relative recovers.

64
00:12:19,160 --> 00:12:20,400
Do you need her for something?

65
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:28,760
Well, Rin's your bodyguard.

66
00:12:28,840 --> 00:12:30,440
If she's gone, I have to ask you.

67
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:08,520
Excuse me. Have you seen the guy
who came with me?

68
00:13:23,400 --> 00:13:24,920
I was wondering where you were.

69
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:28,160
I saw this wasn't being used.
The workers said I could use it.

70
00:13:29,840 --> 00:13:33,440
Got so much free time
that you're designing and sewing clothes?

71
00:13:35,360 --> 00:13:36,840
It's easy, actually.

72
00:13:52,560 --> 00:13:53,600
You made two?

73
00:14:05,520 --> 00:14:06,640
Yes.

74
00:14:07,640 --> 00:14:09,320
I made two shirts.

75
00:14:11,760 --> 00:14:12,880
For a couple.

76
00:14:15,280 --> 00:14:16,280
Not a chance.

77
00:14:17,880 --> 00:14:21,640
I learned it somewhere.
They say if you have a pair of items,

78
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:24,080
that means it's for couples.

79
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:26,040
More like enemies.

80
00:14:28,240 --> 00:14:30,440
Here. Try it on.

81
00:14:33,200 --> 00:14:35,880
Trust me, it'll fit you perfectly.

82
00:14:46,080 --> 00:14:47,360
Whenever you wear it,

83
00:14:48,120 --> 00:14:49,800
it'll remind you of your happy time here.

84
00:15:03,520 --> 00:15:04,640
Do you like it?

85
00:15:23,120 --> 00:15:25,640
So, have you found out anything
about the test tube?

86
00:15:25,720 --> 00:15:28,720
Not yet. The lab said they'd send me
the results as soon as possible.

87
00:15:35,960 --> 00:15:37,440
And when's that?

88
00:15:37,520 --> 00:15:39,200
I said soon.

89
00:15:46,680 --> 00:15:48,200
I could finally reach Taiga.

90
00:15:49,280 --> 00:15:50,400
Where are they?

91
00:15:51,280 --> 00:15:52,440
He didn't tell me.

92
00:15:53,080 --> 00:15:54,680
Why not?

93
00:15:55,520 --> 00:15:58,360
They probably want to be all lovey-dovey.

94
00:16:02,280 --> 00:16:03,120
Madam!

95
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:04,600
You kick hard, madam.

96
00:16:04,680 --> 00:16:07,760
That was my hand, idiot!
Next time, I'll kill you.

97
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:14,840
Hey, you!

98
00:16:14,920 --> 00:16:18,640
Stop joking around and spouting nonsense!
You're giving my friend a bad rap.

99
00:16:18,720 --> 00:16:20,040
Here's two more.

100
00:16:23,160 --> 00:16:24,440
I can't believe them.

101
00:16:26,680 --> 00:16:28,520
It's true, yet you say it's nonsense.

102
00:16:33,440 --> 00:16:36,280
How are things over there?
About me and Rin, I mean.

103
00:16:36,360 --> 00:16:37,680
<i>I'm in big trouble.</i>

104
00:16:37,760 --> 00:16:39,760
Ratee won't stop complaining.

105
00:16:39,840 --> 00:16:41,200
I'm going home now.

106
00:16:41,840 --> 00:16:44,160
Have you learned anything from Rin?

107
00:16:46,440 --> 00:16:47,800
<i>Ratee had her lab</i>

108
00:16:47,880 --> 00:16:50,240
separate the mixture
Aru stole from the lab,

109
00:16:50,960 --> 00:16:52,640
and Techut's been crazy over Aru.

110
00:16:52,720 --> 00:16:53,960
Be careful.

111
00:17:07,240 --> 00:17:08,400
Hey.

112
00:17:09,520 --> 00:17:12,880
Check out that new kid. He's so hot.

113
00:17:12,960 --> 00:17:14,520
I wish he was in our team.

114
00:17:27,720 --> 00:17:29,120
Hello, Mr. Techut.

115
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:32,840
Here’s the summary for Start Up Star
and the revenue, and also,

116
00:17:32,920 --> 00:17:35,800
here's the follower counts of each person,
like you asked.

117
00:17:44,640 --> 00:17:46,320
If there's nothing else, go back to work.

118
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:49,480
Okay.

119
00:18:20,440 --> 00:18:24,000
Hey! Why isn't it done yet?
Hurry up, for God's sake.

120
00:18:24,080 --> 00:18:26,160
I hate waiting.

121
00:18:34,280 --> 00:18:37,400
Oops, I'm sorry.

122
00:18:38,680 --> 00:18:42,560
Would you like coffee?
I'll go serve it to you in your room.

123
00:18:43,960 --> 00:18:44,800
Yeah.

124
00:18:58,360 --> 00:18:59,360
SUMMARY REPORT
CCC CORP

125
00:18:59,440 --> 00:19:00,560
Here you go.

126
00:19:05,080 --> 00:19:07,040
You’re good at making amends.

127
00:19:12,880 --> 00:19:14,560
What did I do wrong?

128
00:19:22,120 --> 00:19:23,360
Where are you moving to?

129
00:19:29,640 --> 00:19:32,760
It's just that my dad
wants me to stay with him.

130
00:19:33,320 --> 00:19:36,040
You know how old people are.
Lonely and ill.

131
00:19:36,560 --> 00:19:38,640
That's why they want their kids around.

132
00:19:43,120 --> 00:19:44,680
I've been gone for too long.

133
00:19:44,760 --> 00:19:46,960
My team downstairs
will think I'm slacking off.

134
00:19:47,760 --> 00:19:49,040
Forget them.

135
00:19:50,280 --> 00:19:51,880
I don't think I can.

136
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:54,640
Lately, they're always
rushing me about work.

137
00:19:54,720 --> 00:19:58,000
They're nudging me every minute.
I can't finish work in time.

138
00:20:01,240 --> 00:20:02,440
Please?

139
00:20:03,040 --> 00:20:04,320
I'll come back up.

140
00:20:13,600 --> 00:20:15,000
I'll get back to work now.

141
00:20:15,920 --> 00:20:17,040
Okay.

142
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:38,200
3C world project documents.

143
00:20:38,280 --> 00:20:42,080
3C-Coin deal documents. Chemical report.

144
00:20:43,240 --> 00:20:44,680
I saw the words,

145
00:20:44,760 --> 00:20:49,520
"Precursor, GP120 HIV Protein."

146
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:01,840
- How'd it go today?
- Yeah.

147
00:21:01,920 --> 00:21:03,080
- Let me see.
- We got a lot.

148
00:21:05,440 --> 00:21:06,960
- Whoa.
- Yeah.

149
00:21:07,040 --> 00:21:08,840
- Today's batch looks great.
- Yes.

150
00:21:08,920 --> 00:21:11,280
- Is there still any left in the orchard?
- Yes, sir.

151
00:21:11,880 --> 00:21:13,560
- Okay.
- We'll pick the rest tomorrow.

152
00:21:14,200 --> 00:21:15,920
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

153
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:19,160
How's everyone doing?

154
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:21,360
Tired, right?

155
00:21:23,200 --> 00:21:25,080
Oh, Auntie! Let me help you.

156
00:21:26,120 --> 00:21:28,240
Today's batch looks so good.

157
00:21:28,320 --> 00:21:29,200
Here.

158
00:21:30,040 --> 00:21:33,800
What? Auntie? Auntie!

159
00:21:34,440 --> 00:21:38,160
Auntie? Auntie, Auntie!

160
00:21:38,240 --> 00:21:41,720
Auntie? Let me fan you. Auntie!

161
00:22:02,360 --> 00:22:03,520
Is the doctor almost here?

162
00:22:13,920 --> 00:22:15,040
Indhorn,

163
00:22:16,240 --> 00:22:19,440
looks like I'll have to visit you, cousin.

164
00:22:25,480 --> 00:22:26,320
Have some water.

165
00:22:44,760 --> 00:22:45,880
Let me see.

166
00:23:06,120 --> 00:23:08,200
Looks like an insect sting, but it's not.

167
00:23:19,160 --> 00:23:21,520
Rin! Rin.

168
00:23:23,360 --> 00:23:24,360
Rin?

169
00:23:27,560 --> 00:23:28,760
Rin.

170
00:24:11,080 --> 00:24:12,400
Same symptoms as my workers.

171
00:24:14,560 --> 00:24:15,800
Your workers are like this too?

172
00:24:16,600 --> 00:24:17,640
Yeah.

173
00:24:17,720 --> 00:24:19,760
I've asked the other workers.

174
00:24:20,840 --> 00:24:23,360
They said she picked corn
with that group of workers.

175
00:24:26,920 --> 00:24:28,000
Same symptoms.

176
00:24:29,160 --> 00:24:31,480
I'm still not sure what's wrong with her.

177
00:24:31,560 --> 00:24:33,800
I've never seen symptoms like this before.

178
00:24:33,880 --> 00:24:35,640
I took everyone's blood samples, though.

179
00:24:35,720 --> 00:24:38,520
I'll call you as soon
as we get the results.

180
00:24:39,600 --> 00:24:40,760
Thank you so much.

181
00:25:28,320 --> 00:25:29,400
What's that formula?

182
00:25:33,560 --> 00:25:35,920
GP120 HIV Protein.

183
00:25:37,040 --> 00:25:37,960
And?

184
00:25:39,040 --> 00:25:41,840
It's the precursor used in Techut's lab.

185
00:25:42,360 --> 00:25:44,160
They're doing some kind of experiment.

186
00:25:45,200 --> 00:25:46,800
Maybe a biological weapon.

187
00:25:47,840 --> 00:25:48,760
A poison?

188
00:25:48,840 --> 00:25:52,680
We still can't conclude.
We have too little information.

189
00:25:54,280 --> 00:25:56,240
So we need Aru to gather more?

190
00:25:56,320 --> 00:25:58,000
Yeah.

191
00:25:58,520 --> 00:26:01,280
But it's very dangerous.

192
00:26:01,360 --> 00:26:04,240
If she messes up, she's done for.

193
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:31,800
"GP120 HIV PROTEIN"

194
00:26:34,320 --> 00:26:35,800
That's what I saw on Techut's desk.

195
00:27:00,440 --> 00:27:01,960
Which department do you work in?

196
00:27:04,000 --> 00:27:05,360
What are you doing on this floor?

197
00:27:08,400 --> 00:27:11,360
Mr. Techut told me to report to him,

198
00:27:11,440 --> 00:27:12,720
but I got here too late.

199
00:27:13,400 --> 00:27:15,960
Report? Report what?

200
00:27:17,400 --> 00:27:20,120
He told me to report it to him alone.

201
00:27:21,920 --> 00:27:23,000
What's your name again?

202
00:27:23,880 --> 00:27:25,120
You're new here, aren't you?

203
00:27:26,040 --> 00:27:27,000
Yes.

204
00:27:27,560 --> 00:27:29,440
My name is Arunothai.

205
00:27:35,280 --> 00:27:36,120
You can go now.

206
00:28:55,160 --> 00:28:57,160
What did he ask you to do?

207
00:28:57,920 --> 00:29:01,920
Does it have anything to do
with GP120 HIV protein?

208
00:29:02,880 --> 00:29:05,080
Well, not really.

209
00:29:05,160 --> 00:29:08,120
I just worked on stuff
like investment reports

210
00:29:08,200 --> 00:29:11,520
or updates on cryptocurrency, DeFi,

211
00:29:11,600 --> 00:29:14,080
and NFT from each source,
then I gave it to him.

212
00:29:16,400 --> 00:29:18,640
I wonder what he's trying to do.

213
00:29:19,680 --> 00:29:22,480
He's gathering all the celebrities.

214
00:29:22,560 --> 00:29:25,960
He probably wants more people
to invest in 3C-coins.

215
00:29:34,080 --> 00:29:35,200
Aru,

216
00:29:36,080 --> 00:29:38,960
let me know
if you need my help with anything.

217
00:29:39,840 --> 00:29:41,320
I'd do anything for you.

218
00:29:50,360 --> 00:29:52,200
Did you text Taiga yet?

219
00:29:54,280 --> 00:29:55,400
I did.

220
00:29:55,480 --> 00:29:58,600
He hasn't read it.
He's probably tied up with something.

221
00:29:58,680 --> 00:29:59,880
You mean with Rin?

222
00:30:04,440 --> 00:30:08,360
I meant with work.
I didn't mean something else!

223
00:30:10,440 --> 00:30:12,320
We can't just keep waiting like this.

224
00:30:13,400 --> 00:30:14,400
Dhammatat,

225
00:30:14,480 --> 00:30:16,040
tell me. Where's Taiga?

226
00:30:17,720 --> 00:30:21,000
I told you I don't know.
We're lucky he even picked up.

227
00:30:21,080 --> 00:30:22,200
You know.

228
00:30:22,840 --> 00:30:25,600
You just won't say it.
You're keeping it a secret from me.

229
00:30:27,680 --> 00:30:28,720
Tell me right now.

230
00:30:29,480 --> 00:30:30,640
Tell me now, Dhammatat.

231
00:30:30,720 --> 00:30:33,000
Speak! I told you to speak.

232
00:30:33,080 --> 00:30:34,480
Tell me where Taiga is right now!

233
00:30:34,560 --> 00:30:36,000
- Madam!
- Speak!

234
00:30:36,080 --> 00:30:38,120
I won't be a witness
in this bear murder case.

235
00:30:38,840 --> 00:30:41,200
- Why are you quiet? Speak!
- Hey, help me!

236
00:30:41,280 --> 00:30:44,480
- Speak! I told you to tell me.
- Hey!

237
00:30:47,680 --> 00:30:49,920
Taiga is probably with Rin somewhere.

238
00:30:51,200 --> 00:30:53,760
Aru, why don't you call Rin?

239
00:30:55,760 --> 00:30:56,760
She turned off her phone.

240
00:30:58,000 --> 00:30:59,120
Then just wait.

241
00:30:59,640 --> 00:31:02,160
Those two wouldn't mess around
for no good reason.

242
00:31:02,240 --> 00:31:05,440
They went quiet because they want us
to wait and for us to be safe.

243
00:31:06,640 --> 00:31:09,160
If you're so eager,
or if your jealousy's killing you,

244
00:31:09,720 --> 00:31:11,520
then go find them yourself.

245
00:32:49,640 --> 00:32:51,360
Rin. Rin!

246
00:32:52,160 --> 00:32:53,120
Rin.

247
00:32:59,120 --> 00:33:00,600
You need to go back to 3C.

248
00:33:02,080 --> 00:33:03,320
I won't leave you.

249
00:33:05,680 --> 00:33:06,640
I'm sick.

250
00:33:07,160 --> 00:33:08,800
You'll contract it.

251
00:33:13,680 --> 00:33:14,920
I'll wait for you, Rin.

252
00:33:16,520 --> 00:33:18,720
I need to know what's wrong
with you and those workers.

253
00:33:20,720 --> 00:33:22,560
The doctor's running tests
with your blood.

254
00:33:27,520 --> 00:33:28,960
You have to get better, Rin.

255
00:33:31,080 --> 00:33:32,840
Get better and fight me again.

256
00:33:57,880 --> 00:33:59,720
The air here is refreshing, as always.

257
00:34:03,560 --> 00:34:06,120
Indhorn. You're still with us?

258
00:34:15,280 --> 00:34:16,120
What's up?

259
00:34:16,760 --> 00:34:18,440
You look like you've seen a ghost.

260
00:34:20,400 --> 00:34:22,520
It's been a while
since I last visited Uncle Narumit.

261
00:34:23,199 --> 00:34:24,120
How's he doing?

262
00:34:24,199 --> 00:34:25,360
Nothing's changed.

263
00:34:26,440 --> 00:34:28,320
Do you want to head inside now?

264
00:34:28,400 --> 00:34:31,400
Not yet. I rarely
get to take a vacation here.

265
00:34:31,960 --> 00:34:33,760
I want to take a walk and see the farm.

266
00:34:35,480 --> 00:34:36,760
Now's not a good time.

267
00:34:38,800 --> 00:34:39,719
Because…

268
00:34:40,480 --> 00:34:42,199
my workers are sick.

269
00:34:42,280 --> 00:34:44,960
No one knows why,
so I quarantined them in a house

270
00:34:45,480 --> 00:34:46,800
in case it's a deadly disease.

271
00:34:47,400 --> 00:34:49,840
Hey, when you're the boss,

272
00:34:49,920 --> 00:34:52,320
you have to take good care
of all your workers.

273
00:34:53,080 --> 00:34:55,560
Where are those sick workers?
Let me see them.

274
00:34:57,360 --> 00:34:58,680
I don't think you should.

275
00:34:59,480 --> 00:35:00,400
It's pretty bad.

276
00:35:00,480 --> 00:35:02,920
Hey, hey. You can't do that.

277
00:35:03,440 --> 00:35:07,000
I'm the CEO at 3C.
I have a thousand employees,

278
00:35:07,680 --> 00:35:10,080
yet I can still take care of them
like they're family.

279
00:35:10,880 --> 00:35:12,120
Your farm's not that big,

280
00:35:12,920 --> 00:35:15,280
so don't say you can't.

281
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:16,960
Yeah?

282
00:35:17,720 --> 00:35:20,800
Where are the sick workers?
Take me to them.

283
00:35:39,760 --> 00:35:42,440
Oh, have you run a blood test
or a physical exam?

284
00:35:43,480 --> 00:35:44,560
Yes,

285
00:35:45,240 --> 00:35:46,960
but the doctor said
everything looked normal.

286
00:35:50,600 --> 00:35:52,320
Then you should take good care of them.

287
00:35:53,240 --> 00:35:55,040
If you need anything, just let me know.

288
00:35:56,560 --> 00:35:58,560
As for the bills for these five people,

289
00:35:59,440 --> 00:36:00,520
I'll pay them for you.

290
00:36:01,040 --> 00:36:03,760
Compensate their family too.

291
00:36:04,760 --> 00:36:06,000
Don't worry about it.

292
00:36:06,920 --> 00:36:10,120
They should get better soon. I've got it.

293
00:36:11,600 --> 00:36:12,760
Don't be arrogant.

294
00:36:13,280 --> 00:36:14,720
You need money for your dad's treatment.

295
00:36:16,560 --> 00:36:19,440
When I trade coins,
I get millions of baht of profits.

296
00:36:19,520 --> 00:36:20,640
This is nothing for me.

297
00:36:21,160 --> 00:36:22,360
Just let me help you.

298
00:36:23,320 --> 00:36:24,880
Your dad is my uncle too.

299
00:36:28,240 --> 00:36:29,640
Okay.

300
00:36:31,040 --> 00:36:32,440
How are things at the farm?

301
00:36:36,760 --> 00:36:39,280
I'll have my workers prepare
a guest suite at the main house.

302
00:36:39,360 --> 00:36:40,200
INSEE RESIDENCE 1

303
00:36:40,280 --> 00:36:41,920
I can stay at the resort on the farm.

304
00:36:43,120 --> 00:36:44,080
Actually,

305
00:36:44,760 --> 00:36:46,680
now's not a good time.
We have guests there.

306
00:36:47,800 --> 00:36:50,880
You should stay at my house.
It's more private.

307
00:36:56,680 --> 00:36:57,840
Mr. Techut.

308
00:37:03,160 --> 00:37:04,480
This is Ms. Ratee.

309
00:37:04,560 --> 00:37:06,280
She's the daughter of Mr. Robert,

310
00:37:06,360 --> 00:37:08,400
the media mogul who's investing with 3C.

311
00:37:09,520 --> 00:37:10,560
Ms. Ratee,

312
00:37:11,080 --> 00:37:12,920
this is Indhorn. He's my cousin.

313
00:37:14,720 --> 00:37:16,120
Hello, Mr. Indhorn.

314
00:37:16,640 --> 00:37:18,000
This place is very pretty.

315
00:37:18,680 --> 00:37:19,720
Thank you.

316
00:37:20,920 --> 00:37:22,640
There's a resort here too.

317
00:37:22,720 --> 00:37:24,280
We're staying here tonight.

318
00:38:36,680 --> 00:38:38,240
They have horses here too?

319
00:38:39,240 --> 00:38:42,440
I haven't ridden one
since I got back from France.

320
00:38:44,080 --> 00:38:45,360
Then,

321
00:38:45,440 --> 00:38:47,720
wanna ride tonight?

322
00:39:21,640 --> 00:39:24,360
Techut's doing some kind of experiment
in the basement.

323
00:39:25,800 --> 00:39:27,720
I saw the text Dhammatat sent.

324
00:39:28,800 --> 00:39:29,920
It's some sort of chemical.

325
00:39:33,440 --> 00:39:35,200
That's why I'm shadowing him.

326
00:39:35,280 --> 00:39:37,080
He wanted to come,

327
00:39:38,040 --> 00:39:39,560
so I asked if I could come too.

328
00:39:42,160 --> 00:39:44,120
But I didn't expect to see you here.

329
00:39:48,520 --> 00:39:49,880
What's he doing here at the farm?

330
00:39:50,600 --> 00:39:51,720
Where else has he been to?

331
00:39:53,960 --> 00:39:55,640
He said he's here
to visit the sick workers.

332
00:39:57,560 --> 00:39:58,560
Rin's sick too.

333
00:39:59,240 --> 00:40:02,080
She got sick at the same time as them,
same symptoms and all,

334
00:40:02,160 --> 00:40:03,680
but we still can't find the cause.

335
00:40:07,400 --> 00:40:08,560
Could it be

336
00:40:08,640 --> 00:40:12,000
that Techut's using the workers here
for his experiment in the basement?

337
00:40:30,360 --> 00:40:32,600
Are you done? I'm melting over here.

338
00:40:34,120 --> 00:40:35,600
Let me do one last check.

339
00:40:59,760 --> 00:41:00,840
Finally.

340
00:41:02,480 --> 00:41:04,520
Mom, the AC's fixed now.

341
00:41:04,600 --> 00:41:05,640
You're all set.

342
00:41:21,160 --> 00:41:22,360
Try this tea.

343
00:41:25,200 --> 00:41:27,080
- It smells so good, Mom.
- Right?

344
00:41:39,160 --> 00:41:40,000
I'm sorry.

345
00:41:46,280 --> 00:41:48,400
I think this color kind of suits you.

346
00:41:49,760 --> 00:41:52,040
But how about this color? Do you like it?

347
00:41:52,120 --> 00:41:53,160
This one?

348
00:41:53,240 --> 00:41:56,480
It might make my skin look too dark.

349
00:41:56,560 --> 00:41:58,040
But I do like it.

350
00:42:01,480 --> 00:42:02,320
What's wrong?

351
00:42:03,600 --> 00:42:04,600
Nothing.

352
00:42:05,440 --> 00:42:08,480
See, it'll be this color…

353
00:42:48,280 --> 00:42:49,120
Yes?

354
00:42:49,200 --> 00:42:50,320
Where are you, Ratee?

355
00:42:50,960 --> 00:42:52,960
Let's have lunch together.

356
00:42:54,360 --> 00:42:56,960
I'm out walking on the farm.
I'll see you in a bit.

357
00:42:57,600 --> 00:42:58,480
Okay.

358
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:06,520
Please be careful, Ratee.

359
00:43:10,760 --> 00:43:11,920
Don't stay the night.

360
00:43:12,720 --> 00:43:14,240
Find a way to return to Bangkok tonight.

361
00:43:16,360 --> 00:43:17,840
Please tell Dhammatat to hurry

362
00:43:18,720 --> 00:43:20,880
and find out what Techut's experiment is.

363
00:43:44,600 --> 00:43:47,080
<i>Honey, can I help you with anything else</i>

364
00:43:47,160 --> 00:43:48,720
on the Hi app?

365
00:43:48,800 --> 00:43:50,520
I'm tired of staying home doing nothing.

366
00:43:50,600 --> 00:43:53,040
There are more things to do
in our building. It's more fun.

367
00:43:53,120 --> 00:43:54,440
You don't have to think.

368
00:43:55,160 --> 00:43:56,400
I'll tell you what to do.

369
00:44:24,080 --> 00:44:25,440
I have to leave right away.

370
00:44:25,520 --> 00:44:27,600
My father flew here to surprise me.

371
00:44:27,680 --> 00:44:29,400
Then, let me give you a ride,

372
00:44:30,400 --> 00:44:31,880
so I can meet your father too.

373
00:44:32,480 --> 00:44:33,520
That's alright.

374
00:44:34,440 --> 00:44:37,600
I've never told my dad about you.
I don't want to shock him.

375
00:44:37,680 --> 00:44:39,200
What's so shocking about it?

376
00:44:39,280 --> 00:44:41,080
I'm no ordinary man.

377
00:44:41,160 --> 00:44:42,720
He just has to look up my name,

378
00:44:42,800 --> 00:44:45,680
then he'll know how special I am.

379
00:44:51,280 --> 00:44:52,960
No, it's just the way he is.

380
00:44:54,800 --> 00:44:56,560
Let me talk to him first.

381
00:44:57,720 --> 00:45:00,480
Once he knows I like you a lot,

382
00:45:01,640 --> 00:45:03,440
we can have dinner together,

383
00:45:03,520 --> 00:45:05,680
then you can talk about golfing

384
00:45:05,760 --> 00:45:08,360
and a couple of things about business.

385
00:45:13,560 --> 00:45:15,360
It's because that's what you think!

386
00:45:15,440 --> 00:45:16,760
That's why you adopted Rin,

387
00:45:16,840 --> 00:45:18,800
despite killing his father

388
00:45:18,880 --> 00:45:20,160
and your own senior!

389
00:45:20,240 --> 00:45:22,080
<i>Techut's fingerprint is on here.</i>

390
00:45:22,160 --> 00:45:24,520
<i>Hurry and collect it,</i>
<i>so we can enter the lab.</i>

391
00:45:28,880 --> 00:45:30,160
- No!
- No!

392
00:45:30,240 --> 00:45:32,000
Don't let Taiga out of the 3C building.

393
00:45:34,800 --> 00:45:38,280
Why do all these nice things for me?
We'll have to kill each other anyway.

394
00:46:08,400 --> 00:46:09,920
Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya
